ss for reading text files in the streaming API. The javadoc (lines 33-35) indicates: \\\"If you want to read/write data from/to text file, please use FLIP-27 FileSource and Sink-V2 FlinkSink. This class should be removed if we drop the supports for read/write via input/output format in DataStream api.\\\" Marked with @Deprecated at line 37.\\n\\n3. **TextOutputFormat** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextOutputFormat.java) - An I/O format class for writing text files in the streaming API. The javadoc (lines 37-40) indicates: \\\"If you want to read/write data from/to text file, please use FLIP-27 FileSource and Sink-V2 FlinkSink. This class should be removed if we drop all supports for InputFormat and OutputFormat.\\\" Marked with @Deprecated at line 42.\\n\\nAll three deprecated classes are found in the flink-streaming-java module under either the timestamps (timestamp extractors) or legacy/io (I/O format classes) packages.\"\n}\n",
